<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7605> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7605" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Leg., lieut. 43-42. In MRR 2.366, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.516-517, no. 505, 43-42 B.C. He served under C. Cassius Imp. (59) and Q. Caepio Brutus Imp. (53). See Syme, Hermes 92, 1964, 410; and Sherk, RDGE no. 27, pp. 158-162.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6197> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6197" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate who served under Brutus and Cassius in 43 and 42 (Grueber, CRRBM 2.483f.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6049> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6049" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Along with other Tribunes he called the Senate meeting on December 20, 44, in order to provide for protection for the meeting on January 1, 43, and thus roused Cicero to take a lead in opposing Antony (Cic. Phil. 4.16). Early in March he gave Cicero the platform in a public meeting to discuss his proposal to give Cassius the supreme command in the East against Dolabella (Cic. Fam. 12.7.1; cf. Ad Brut. 2.5.3)." .
